<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-09T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-09T22:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Portugal/854:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-09T23:00:00-04:00">April 9,
                                    1943—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>618. Your 744, April 3, 11 a.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d456fn30">Not
                                printed.</note> Immediately upon conclusion of surcharge
                            controversy, it is requested that you open negotiations on wolfram
                            agreement along lines detailed in the Department’s 228 of February 12, 7
                            p.m. If your British colleague lacks parallel instructions, or if in
                            your judgment intervening events require an altered approach, please
                            telegraph urgently.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>